{
  "stem": "543.1",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We had to take-- we-- my parents lived already in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They lived in Amsterdam.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They moved them out of the place, and gave them another place to live in the-- they call it the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was like a couple streets.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They called it the ghetto, actually.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And so we were only two days by my mother in-- in-- in Amsterdam and the Dutch police, who was already-- they were still good.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They was not overtaken by the SS's.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we had a lot-- we had also [INAUDIBLE] in Holland, a lot of people, sympathizers, Nazi sympathizers who were police, I think.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And those Dutch police took us in the night out of my mother's place, and I said, you go there and there are friends of ours.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So soon we came in a house, they said right away, they said, oh, yeah.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You can stay with us.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yeah, when we were still in Haamstede, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] when-- when we were still in Haamstede, we had-- we had people who were-- said why don't you take some false papers and maybe you can-- you don't have to-- we had a big star on-- the Jewish star on our passport.",
      "word_count": 54
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they made us false papers without-- without-- a false name and also no star on it.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But I was still afraid to go.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Everybody knew me in Haamstede.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I was still afraid.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I never used them.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then-- and then we-- I went into hiding.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Over a year and a half.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "First, we went to our-- the grocery-- the guy from the grocery store who always had a horse and a wagon, who came out and was talking to us, and said-- but he had five kids, and he had another friend.",
      "word_count": 41
    }
  ],
